ReSea.message: I come to view the boundless ocean,<n>From Stony Hill on eastern shore.<n>Its water rolls in rhythmic motion,<n>And islands stand amid its roar.<n>Tree on tree grows from peak to peak;<n>Grass on grass looks lush far and nigh.<n>The autumn wind blows drear and bleak;<n>The monstrous billows surge up high.<n>The sun by day, the moon by night,<n>Appear to rise up from the deep.<n>The Milky Way with stars so bright,<n>Sinks down into the sea in sleep.<n>How happy I feel at this sight!I croon this poem in delight.
ReSea.title: The Sea
